    • shift

      public static <T> void shift​(T[] arr, int... stopPoints)
      Moves the elements in the specified array over so that null elements moved to the back of the array, and non-null elements are moved to the front.

      The stop points "split" the array into sub-arrays, and each null element in each sub-array will be moved to the back of their sub-array.

      So for example, if you specify 3 as a stop point, no elements from 0-3 will be moved greater than 3, and no elements from 4-infinity will be moved less than 4.

      Leave the stop points array blank to shift all elements in the array.

      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of elements inside the array.
      Parameters:
      arr - The array being shifted.
      stopPoints - The array of stop points.

    • shiftExact

      public static <T> boolean shiftExact​(T[] arr, int minIndex, int maxIndex, int spaces, boolean safe)
      Shifts the elements defined by the specified min and max indexes in the specified array to the left the specified number of spaces.
      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of elements inside the array.
      Parameters:
      arr - The array.
      minIndex - The minimum (inclusive) index.
      maxIndex - The maximum (exclusive) index. Specify -1 for no max index (the end of the array).
      spaces - The number of spaces the elements are being shifted.
      safe - True if the operation should be done only if the operation can be safely completed without overwriting any non-null elements, false otherwise.
      Returns:
      True if the shift was successful, false otherwise.

    • spread

      public static <T> boolean spread​(T[] arr, int index, int spaces, boolean safe)
      Makes space in the specified array at the specified index of the specified size. The space is made by moving existing elements to the right.

      spaces - The number of indexes in which the space should take up.
      safe - True if the operation should be done only if the operation can be safely completed without overwriting any non-null elements, false otherwise.
      Returns:
      True if the space was made, false otherwise.

    • place

      @SafeVarargs public static <T> void place​(T[] arr, ArrayTools.PlaceElement<T>... elements)
      Inserts the specified PlaceElements inside the specified array.

      Each PlaceElement is placed into the specified array under the following conditions:

      1. The index is between the calculated minimum and maximum indexes (see below)
      2. The index is non-null.
      The minimum index is always set to the index specified by the PlaceElement.

      If the PlaceElement is the last element in the PlaceElement array, then the maximum index is set to arr.length - 1. In all other scenarios, the maximum index is set to the index specified by the next PlaceElement in PlaceElement array.

      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of elements inside the array.
      Parameters:
      arr - The array.
      elements - The PlaceElements.

    • move

      public static <T> boolean move​(T[] arr1, T[] arr2, int index1, int index2, int stopShiftAt, boolean safe)
      Moves an element from the first specified array to the second specified array.
      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of elements inside the array.
      Parameters:
      arr1 - The first array (the array being moved from).
      arr2 - The second array (the array being moved to).
      index1 - The index of the element being moved from the first array.
      index2 - The index in which the element from the first array is being moved to in the second array.
      stopShiftAt - The index (max) in which elements should stop being shifted in the first array after the element has been removed. Specify -1 to remove until the end of the array, or 0 to not move at all.
      safe - True if the operation should be done only if the operation can be safely completed without overwriting any non-null elements, false otherwise.
      Returns:
      True if the element was successfully moved, false otherwise.
